President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 18, 2012, as National Defense Transportation Day and May 13-19, 2012, as National Transportation Week. In the proclamation, President Obama emphasizes the importance of transportation infrastructure in fueling the nation's growth and economy. He highlights the need for strong and sustainable transportation networks and acknowledges the competitive disadvantage created by crumbling bridges and outdated infrastructure. The proclamation also mentions the administration's efforts to invest in long-term transportation infrastructure projects through initiatives like the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act and the Transportation Investment Generating Economic Recovery (TIGER) Discretionary Grant program. President Obama calls upon all Americans to recognize the contributions of those involved in building, operating, and maintaining the nation's transportation infrastructure.